Bayesian A/B Testing Tutorial

Rain Wang

2/13/2021

Binary

Data

  • A is simulated from 250 binomial data points with p=0.3.
  • B is simulated from 250 binomial data points with p=0.2.
A_binom Freq
0 184
1 66
B_binom Freq
0 192
1 58

Prior Distribution

  • Parameter = Probability
  • Probability ~ Beta(a, b)

Test Result

The probability of P(A > B) by 5% is 0.55.

90% credible interval of (A - B) = (-0.11, 0.28).

Posterior Expected Loss of choosing B over A = 0.02.

Summary

Poisson

Data

  • A is simulated from 250 poisson data points with lambda=6.
  • B is simulated from 250 poisson data points with lambda=6.

Prior Distribution

  • Parameter = Lambda
  • Lambda ~ Gamma(a, b)

Test Result

The probability of P(A > B) by 1% is 0.15.

90% credible interval of (A - B) = (-0.08, 0.03).

Posterior Expected Loss of choosing B over A = 0.03.

Summary
